	/>

	<ArticleSection number="04" title="Living With It">
		<p>
			None of this is really about winning an argument with a cartoon. It's about a car that's quietly excellent
			and constantly overlooked, mostly because the culture decided its little brother was the one worth
			remembering. Take it up through Hakone's switchbacks — actual elevation change, actual corners — and it stops
			being a trivia answer and starts being just a genuinely good, characterful, slightly unhinged old turbo coupe
			that happens to also be a great-looking piece of early-80s design.
		</p>
		<p>It doesn't need the Initial D cameo to be worth driving. It probably would have been better with one.</p>
	</ArticleSection>

	<ImageGrid
		variant="wide"
		tiles={[
			{
